{"TopicId":49443,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[Airships in 1.12.3] HooliganLabs Mods","CreatedByName":"JewelShisen","CreatedById":71737,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-10-19T15:34:37Z","PageNum":46,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"KOCOUR","CreatedById":37749,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-24T13:37:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI only use this one Airship mod, so it has to be part of it. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RedParadize","CreatedById":129285,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-24T14:15:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222815352\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002249443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477005288\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022106975\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Angel-125\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/20/2016 at 7:14 PM, Angel-125 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaking progress, got the large, medium, and small dirigible sections done, and just (nearly) finished the gyro ring:By default, the fuel tank (4500 unit capacity), starts half-full. That way you can use it to pump fuel between gyro rings for use as ballast. I don\u0027t know if HL has an in-flight \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECOL\u003C/abbr\u003E indicator, but if not I plan to add one in the plugin I\u0027m working on. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReally cool! Do you plan on expand on this? It would be awesome to have inflatable version that we can carry to other planets!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kevin Kyle","CreatedById":110492,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-24T14:15:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222820371\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002249443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477268055\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002271737\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JewelShisen\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, JewelShisen said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs soon as I get told the GitHub has been updated I will be happy to push out an update to the mod!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou dont need to do that for me, Ive changed mine already. I just assumed you would update that on the next build. It was the only part with that issue wasnt it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn a side note, I noticed that the contracts have been using the parts from mod for Kerbal rescue missions. All of the others were in Gondolas and its been fine, I did try to bring one back to Kerbin but it quickly succumbed to the heat on re-entry, No big surprise there. I really just wanted to get the part out of orbit. I got enough junk in orbit as it is. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Angelo Kerman","CreatedById":106975,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-24T18:14:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222821092\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002249443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477318509\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129285\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RedParadize\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, RedParadize said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReally cool! Do you plan on expand on this? It would be awesome to have inflatable version that we can carry to other planets!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve thought of that, but need to make the basic components first.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stone Blue","CreatedById":77721,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-24T19:29:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust wondering how feasable it would be to model something like the Airlander for KSP, and if anyone has looked into it?\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hybrid_Air_Vehicles_HAV_304_Airlander_10\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hybrid_Air_Vehicles_HAV_304_Airlander_10\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpannerMonkey(smce)","CreatedById":50907,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-24T19:51:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222821548\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002249443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477337373\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002277721\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Stone Blue\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, Stone Blue said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust wondering how feasable it would be to model something like the Airlander for KSP, and if anyone has looked into it?\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hybrid_Air_Vehicles_HAV_304_Airlander_10\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hybrid_Air_Vehicles_HAV_304_Airlander_10\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHI, I\u0027d imagine it would be as simple as applying a lifting body module to an envelope part.\u00A0\u00A0 you\u0027d have to scupper the HL plugins ability to lift, 50% gas volume would sound right, and see what happens, can\u0027t see an issue aside from getting that gas volume just right( normally we get that directly from the modelling program as cylinder volume)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Eldrad_Ulthran","CreatedById":185228,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-25T03:21:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust found his on the iPad and now want to create a duna\u00A0base with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0mooring. Ugh! I don\u0027t have my pc\u00A0here!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-25T03:22:24Z\u0022 title=\u002210/25/2016 03:22  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Eldrad_Ulthran\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DarkGod","CreatedById":160635,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-25T18:46:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSadly this is broken by Contract Configurator exposing some buggy toolbar code, see there, fix looks simple:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/55420-120-toolbar-1713-common-api-for-draggableresizable-buttons-toolbar/\u0026amp;page=55\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2770188\u0026amp;embedComment=2770188\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-2770188\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JewelShisen","CreatedById":71737,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-25T19:05:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222823108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002249443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477421178\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160635\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DarkGod\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, DarkGod said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSadly this is broken by Contract Configurator exposing some buggy toolbar code, see there, fix looks simple:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/55420-120-toolbar-1713-common-api-for-draggableresizable-buttons-toolbar/\u0026amp;page=55\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2770188\u0026amp;embedComment=2770188\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-2770188\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe know and I have been tossing about the idea of scrapping all connection to the old toolbar mod as it has been made unnessary, in my opinion, by the stock toolbar.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpannerMonkey(smce)","CreatedById":50907,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-25T19:32:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222823134\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002249443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477422300\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002271737\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JewelShisen\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n27 minutes ago, JewelShisen said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe know and I have been tossing about the idea of scrapping all connection to the old toolbar mod as it has been made unnessary, in my opinion, by the stock toolbar.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWorks for me not used blizzy\u0027s since it started spamming compat messages everywhere\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-25T19:33:35Z\u0022 title=\u002210/25/2016 07:33  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by SpannerMonkey(smce)\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"oniontrain","CreatedById":2465,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-27T02:11:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there an option to use the stock toolbar? Clicking on everything is rather hectic without the UI\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JewelShisen","CreatedById":71737,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-27T02:13:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222825361\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002249443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477534285\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00222465\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022oniontrain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, oniontrain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there an option to use the stock toolbar? Clicking on everything is rather hectic without the UI\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe mod uses it by default unless you have the toolbar mod installed (honestly why would anybody at this point?)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"oniontrain","CreatedById":2465,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-27T02:15:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s some stuff that still requires it I have installed... somewhere...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JewelShisen","CreatedById":71737,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-27T02:16:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen you will have to use that. If it even still works...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DigitalProeliator","CreatedById":75677,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-28T21:32:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a way to force it to use the stock toolbar, if Toolbar is installed even right clicking on the part and checking toggle GUI does not bring it up..? There are a few mods where you need the toolbar mod like Docking Port Indicator, and Scansat so there is a reason to have it installed..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-28T21:47:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222823174\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002249443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477423963\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002250907\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpannerMonkey(smce)\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/25/2016 at 3:32 PM, SpannerMonkey(smce) said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWorks for me not used blizzy\u0027s since it started spamming compat messages everywhere\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis Mod needs to get the toolbar wrapper updated and recompile the whole mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a problem which\u00A0was hidden until CC was released for 1.2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JewelShisen","CreatedById":71737,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-28T21:49:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222828025\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002249443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477691255\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis Mod needs to get the toolbar wrapper updated and recompile the whole mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a problem which\u00A0was hidden until CC was released for 1.2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe will be removing toolbar from the mod with the next update.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-28T21:50:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222828028\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002249443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477691376\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002271737\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JewelShisen\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, JewelShisen said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe will be removing toolbar from the mod with the next update.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JewelShisen","CreatedById":71737,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-28T21:51:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222828033\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002249443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477691442\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStock toolbar exists.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-28T21:51:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222828036\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002249443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477691475\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002271737\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JewelShisen\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, JewelShisen said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStock toolbar exists.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, yes sir, but it can get very crowded\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DigitalProeliator","CreatedById":75677,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-28T21:52:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell the only time you need it is if your using a HL based part, then its a simple right click. with a very basic menu. Its not exactly like scansats menu options, and I honestly wonder if ANY toolbar is needed, even the stock one...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JewelShisen","CreatedById":71737,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-30T00:21:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222828039\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002249443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477691562\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002275677\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DigitalProeliator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/28/2016 at 4:52 PM, DigitalProeliator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell the only time you need it is if your using a HL based part, then its a simple right click. with a very basic menu. Its not exactly like scansats menu options, and I honestly wonder if ANY toolbar is needed, even the stock one...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would prefer to leave it in simply for the fact of very large airships making it difficult or awkward to reach the parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CaptKordite","CreatedById":142147,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-30T22:22:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0026gt; I honestly wonder if ANY toolbar is needed, even the stock one\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot that it needs a toolbar, per se, but I\u0027m currently dealing with the conflict with Contract Configrator. With CC installed, I don\u0027t get the HL Toolbar and thus don\u0027t get altitude control. Makes the airships almost completely unflyable. Move those tools to the right-click menu and I I\u0027ll be very happy. I don\u0027t fly planes at all around Kerbin. It\u0027s all airships.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DigitalProeliator","CreatedById":75677,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-31T03:32:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222830986\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002249443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477866148\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022142147\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022CaptKordite\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, CaptKordite said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith CC installed, I don\u0027t get the HL Toolbar and thus don\u0027t get altitude control. Makes the airships almost completely unflyable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know about that. I typically raise each part by 15 until one end goes up, then increase by 5 in the heavy side until the craft is basically horizontal, and then control altitude using the middle parts buoyancy. Doing this in fact let me complete the GAP contract pack Coast Guard certification mission, and find out getting to close to the hikers on the K2 mission will just let them fall to their deaths because they are floating... It is a bit more work, but its totally doable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CaptKordite","CreatedById":142147,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-03T01:29:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInstead of trying to fly craft I built previous, I started from scratch and tried flying them without the GUI. Difficult. Slow. Delicate. But doable. In all honesty, probably a lot more like trying to fly a real airship than clicking a button that automatically maintains an altitude. Definitely need \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E for fine control. Once I have better mastery of smaller craft, I\u0027ll have to try something larger.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u002230108258023_6d606d3b5f_b_d.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022https://farm6.staticflickr.com/5661/30108258023_6d606d3b5f_b_d.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}